						</foundation>
						<name>Strong Army</name>
						<adjective>Rerobaiic</adjective>
						<memberName>Rerobaiite</memberName>
						<leaderTitleMale>Divine Chief</leaderTitleMale>
						<leaderTitleFemale>Divine Chief</leaderTitleFemale>
						<description>The people of the arid world Chelis worshipped &lt;color=#D09B61FF&gt;Rerobai&lt;/color&gt;. He saw that they were suited for creation, and ordained that these worshippers would rule above all others. There was peace, until a chief and his sand-warriors rebelled against &lt;color=#D09B61FF&gt;Rerobai&lt;/color&gt;'s dominion. The Rerobaiites were forced to flee to a hidden water center. A hero named Saiem 'Dragonfly' Leira tried to assassinate the chief. She failed, but &lt;color=#D09B61FF&gt;Rerobai&lt;/color&gt; witnessed Dragonfly's struggle, and anointed her as the prophet of the Rerobaiites. Dragonfly destroyed the capital of Chelis with an archotech mass-inverter, killing the chief. She took her place as ruler of Chelis - and the universe beyond.</description>
						<descriptionTemplate>The people of the arid world Chelis worshipped %%deity0_name%%. %%Deity0_pronoun%% saw that they were suited for creation, and ordained that these worshippers would rule above all others. There was peace, until a chief and his sand-warriors rebelled against %%deity0_name%%'s dominion. The %%memberNamePlural%% were forced to flee to a hidden water center. A hero named Saiem 'Dragonfly' Leira tried to assassinate the chief. She failed, but %%deity0_name%% witnessed Dragonfly's struggle, and anointed her as the prophet of the %%memberNamePlural%%. Dragonfly destroyed the capital of Chelis with an archotech mass-inverter, killing the chief. She took her place as ruler of Chelis - and the universe beyond.</descriptionTemplate>
